@startuml
title CI/CD Flow - GitHub Actions + Terraform + ECR/ECS

actor Developer
participant "GitHub\nRepository" as GitHub
participant "GitHub Actions\n(CI)" as Actions
participant "Container Registry\n(ECR)" as ECR
participant "Terraform\n(Plan Artifact)" as Terraform
participant "Reviewer / Operator" as Reviewer
participant "AWS\n(ECS)" as AWS

Developer -> GitHub: Push (feature branch) / Open PR
GitHub -> Actions: Trigger workflow (on: push, pull_request)

Actions -> Actions: Checkout code
Actions -> Actions: Setup JDK, Gradle
Actions -> Actions: Run `./gradlew test` (Build & Test)

Actions -> Actions: Build Docker image
Actions -> ECR: Authenticate & Push image (tag: ${GITHUB_SHA} / latest)

Actions -> Actions: Prepare Terraform environment (init)
Actions -> Terraform: terraform plan -out=tfplan
Terraform -> Actions: Upload `tfplan` as artifact (plan_run_id)

note right of Actions
  - Plan artifact uploaded for review
  - Workflow posts comment with plan details (optional)
end note

Reviewer -> GitHub: Review PR and inspect `tfplan` artifact
Reviewer -> Actions: Manually trigger Apply workflow (inputs: plan_run_id)

Actions -> Actions: Download `tfplan` artifact
Actions -> Terraform: terraform apply "tfplan"
Terraform -> AWS: Update resources (ECS TaskDefinition, Service rollout)

AWS -> Developer: Deployment / rollout status (via logs or notification)

note over GitHub,Actions
  Optional: OIDC or AWS Secrets used for auth
end note

@enduml

